This paper deals with computational complexity in the context of judgment aggregation, which involves combining individual judgments to form a collective judgment. This topic is closely related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and game theory (cs.GT), as well as logic (cs.LO) and data structures (cs.DS) which are relevant for representing and manipulating judgments. Additionally, the paper discusses the problem of safety in judgment aggregation, which could be seen as a form of verification or validation, making the topic relevant to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
